Take a Jole or Rand, and divide it into four pieces;
ſeaſon it with Salt and grated Nutmeg: ſtick on it a few Cloves, and
faſten it on a ſmall Spit, putting between it a few Bay-leaves; ſtick in
the out-ſide little ſprigs of Roſemary; baſte it with Butter; ſave
the dripping; ſawce it with Butter, Verjuyce, and Juyce of Oranges;
garniſhing it with ſome ſlices.

